      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>On treatment with HBr, vinylcyclohexane undergoes addition and rearrangement to yield 1-bromo-1-ethylcyclohexane. Using curved arrows, propose a mechanism to account for this result.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBc2dSIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--a2643d5c86bd202283ad3a111193bc5c2a8ea21a/OChem_07_11_005.jpg\" alt=\"Vinylcyclohexane reacts with hydrogen bromide to form 1-bromo-1-ethylcyclohexane.\">\n",
